  "prompt": "Which is the best app to make anonymous call online?",
  "response": "As of my latest update in October 2023, several apps and services offer the ability to make anonymous calls online. Determining the \"best\" app will depend on your specific needs and preferences, including factors such as ease of use, features, cost, and privacy levels. Here are some popular choices:\n\n1. **Burner**: Burner allows you to create temporary phone numbers to make and receive calls and texts without revealing your actual number.\n\n2. **Hushed**: Hushed offers temporary phone numbers for anonymous calls and texts. This app provides good privacy features and is easy to use.\n\n3. **TextNow**: TextNow gives you a free phone number for calling and texting. It's not primarily designed for anonymity, but it can provide a layer of privacy for users.\n\n4. **Google Voice**: Google Voice allows you to get a secondary phone number for making calls, although it's linked to your Google account.\n\n5. **Skype**: Skype offers the option to make calls with an anonymous caller ID if you purchase Skype credits.\n\n6. **Signal**: Signal is primarily a secure messaging app, but it also supports voice and video calls with a strong focus on privacy and encryption.\n\nRemember to consider the legal implications and terms of service of any app you use for anonymous calls. It's important to use these tools ethically and responsibly.",
